{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":520,"text":"Chris Anderson:\nElon, hey, welcome back to TED."},{"time":3560,"text":"It's great to have you here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4960,"text":"Elon Musk: Thanks for having me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6560,"text":"CA: So, in the next half hour or so,"},{"time":9440,"text":"we're going to spend some time"},{"time":11280,"text":"exploring your vision for what\nan exciting future might look like,"},{"time":15200,"text":"which I guess makes\nthe first question a little ironic:"},{"time":19320,"text":"Why are you boring?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21080,"text":"EM: Yeah."},{"time":22320,"text":"I ask myself that frequently."},{"time":27240,"text":"We're trying to dig a hole under LA,"},{"time":31400,"text":"and this is to create the beginning"},{"time":34600,"text":"of what will hopefully\nbe a 3D network of tunnels"},{"time":39520,"text":"to alleviate congestion."},{"time":41760,"text":"So right now, one of the most\nsoul-destroying things is traffic."},{"time":47320,"text":"It affects people\nin every part of the world."},{"time":50200,"text":"It takes away so much of your life."},{"time":54040,"text":"It's horrible."},{"time":56040,"text":"It's particularly horrible in LA."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60360,"text":"CA: I think you've brought with you"},{"time":62320,"text":"the first visualization\nthat's been shown of this."},{"time":64800,"text":"Can I show this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66160,"text":"EM: Yeah, absolutely.\nSo this is the first time --"},{"time":68880,"text":"Just to show what we're talking about."},{"time":70760,"text":"So a couple of key things\nthat are important"},{"time":72920,"text":"in having a 3D tunnel network."},{"time":76840,"text":"First of all, you have to be able"},{"time":78480,"text":"to integrate the entrance\nand exit of the tunnel"},{"time":80760,"text":"seamlessly into the fabric of the city."},{"time":82840,"text":"So by having an elevator,"},{"time":86520,"text":"sort of a car skate,\nthat's on an elevator,"},{"time":91320,"text":"you can integrate the entrance\nand exits to the tunnel network"},{"time":95280,"text":"just by using two parking spaces."},{"time":98840,"text":"And then the car gets on a skate."},{"time":100960,"text":"There's no speed limit here,"},{"time":102360,"text":"so we're designing this to be able\nto operate at 200 kilometers an hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107400,"text":"CA: How much?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108640,"text":"EM: 200 kilometers an hour,\nor about 130 miles per hour."},{"time":112800,"text":"So you should be able\nto get from, say, Westwood to LAX"},{"time":119040,"text":"in six minutes -- five, six minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121320,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":125680,"text":"CA: So possibly, initially done,"},{"time":127280,"text":"it's like on a sort\nof toll road-type basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129600,"text":"EM: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130840,"text":"CA: Which, I guess,\nalleviates some traffic"},{"time":132920,"text":"from the surface streets as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134640,"text":"EM: So, I don't know\nif people noticed it in the video,"},{"time":137280,"text":"but there's no real limit\nto how many levels of tunnel you can have."},{"time":142440,"text":"You can go much further deep\nthan you can go up."},{"time":145280,"text":"The deepest mines are much deeper\nthan the tallest buildings are tall,"},{"time":149480,"text":"so you can alleviate any arbitrary\nlevel of urban congestion"},{"time":154760,"text":"with a 3D tunnel network."},{"time":156080,"text":"This is a very important point."},{"time":157640,"text":"So a key rebuttal to the tunnels\nis that if you add one layer of tunnels,"},{"time":164040,"text":"that will simply alleviate congestion,\nit will get used up,"},{"time":166840,"text":"and then you'll be back where you started,\nback with congestion."},{"time":170160,"text":"But you can go to any\narbitrary number of tunnels,"},{"time":172600,"text":"any number of levels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173960,"text":"CA: But people -- seen traditionally,\nit's incredibly expensive to dig,"},{"time":177520,"text":"and that would block this idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179320,"text":"EM: Yeah."},{"time":181040,"text":"Well, they're right."},{"time":182280,"text":"To give you an example,\nthe LA subway extension,"},{"time":186080,"text":"which is -- I think it's\na two-and-a-half mile extension"},{"time":189760,"text":"that was just completed\nfor two billion dollars."},{"time":192023,"text":"So it's roughly a billion dollars a mile\nto do the subway extension in LA."},{"time":197440,"text":"And this is not the highest\nutility subway in the world."},{"time":201440,"text":"So yeah, it's quite difficult\nto dig tunnels normally."},{"time":205960,"text":"I think we need to have\nat least a tenfold improvement"},{"time":209160,"text":"in the cost per mile of tunneling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212160,"text":"CA: And how could you achieve that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216240,"text":"EM: Actually, if you just do two things,"},{"time":218320,"text":"you can get to approximately\nan order of magnitude improvement,"},{"time":221680,"text":"and I think you can go beyond that."},{"time":223880,"text":"So the first thing to do\nis to cut the tunnel diameter"},{"time":228160,"text":"by a factor of two or more."},{"time":229800,"text":"So a single road lane tunnel\naccording to regulations"},{"time":233800,"text":"has to be 26 feet,\nmaybe 28 feet in diameter"},{"time":236680,"text":"to allow for crashes\nand emergency vehicles"},{"time":239880,"text":"and sufficient ventilation\nfor combustion engine cars."},{"time":244160,"text":"But if you shrink that diameter\nto what we're attempting,"},{"time":247760,"text":"which is 12 feet, which is plenty\nto get an electric skate through,"},{"time":251440,"text":"you drop the diameter by a factor of two"},{"time":254680,"text":"and the cross-sectional area\nby a factor of four,"},{"time":258600,"text":"and the tunneling cost scales\nwith the cross-sectional area."},{"time":261480,"text":"So that's roughly a half-order\nof magnitude improvement right there."},{"time":264720,"text":"Then tunneling machines currently tunnel\nfor half the time, then they stop,"},{"time":269640,"text":"and then the rest of the time\nis putting in reinforcements"},{"time":272840,"text":"for the tunnel wall."},{"time":274160,"text":"So if you design the machine instead"},{"time":276400,"text":"to do continuous\ntunneling and reinforcing,"},{"time":278760,"text":"that will give you\na factor of two improvement."},{"time":281000,"text":"Combine that and that's a factor of eight."},{"time":283240,"text":"Also these machines are far from being\nat their power or thermal limits,"},{"time":287920,"text":"so you can jack up the power\nto the machine substantially."},{"time":291000,"text":"I think you can get\nat least a factor of two,"},{"time":293160,"text":"maybe a factor of four or five\nimprovement on top of that."},{"time":297360,"text":"So I think there's a fairly\nstraightforward series of steps"},{"time":301600,"text":"to get somewhere in excess\nof an order of magnitude improvement"},{"time":304600,"text":"in the cost per mile,"},{"time":306360,"text":"and our target actually is --"},{"time":309320,"text":"we've got a pet snail called Gary,"},{"time":312160,"text":"this is from Gary the snail\nfrom \"South Park,\""},{"time":314720,"text":"I mean, sorry, \"SpongeBob SquarePants.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":317680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":319280,"text":"So Gary is capable of --"},{"time":323720,"text":"currently he's capable\nof going 14 times faster"},{"time":327840,"text":"than a tunnel-boring machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":332440,"text":"CA: You want to beat Gary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334240,"text":"EM: We want to beat Gary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337120,"text":"He's not a patient little fellow,"},{"time":339360,"text":"and that will be victory."},{"time":342480,"text":"Victory is beating the snail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345280,"text":"CA: But a lot of people imagining,\ndreaming about future cities,"},{"time":348360,"text":"they imagine that actually\nthe solution is flying cars, drones, etc."},{"time":352280,"text":"You go aboveground."},{"time":354520,"text":"Why isn't that a better solution?"},{"time":356360,"text":"You save all that tunneling cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358360,"text":"EM: Right. I'm in favor of flying things."},{"time":360600,"text":"Obviously, I do rockets,\nso I like things that fly."},{"time":364480,"text":"This is not some inherent bias\nagainst flying things,"},{"time":367440,"text":"but there is a challenge with flying cars"},{"time":370520,"text":"in that they'll be quite noisy,"},{"time":373840,"text":"the wind force generated\nwill be very high."},{"time":380000,"text":"Let's just say that if something's\nflying over your head,"},{"time":382720,"text":"a whole bunch of flying cars\ngoing all over the place,"},{"time":386440,"text":"that is not an anxiety-reducing situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393200,"text":"You don't think to yourself,\n\"Well, I feel better about today.\""},{"time":398520,"text":"You're thinking,\n\"Did they service their hubcap,"},{"time":401160,"text":"or is it going to come off\nand guillotine me?\""},{"time":404080,"text":"Things like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408320,"text":"CA: So you've got this vision"},{"time":409920,"text":"of future cities with these rich,\n3D networks of tunnels underneath."},{"time":415240,"text":"Is there a tie-in here with Hyperloop?"},{"time":417280,"text":"Could you apply these tunnels\nto use for this Hyperloop idea"},{"time":420840,"text":"you released a few years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422840,"text":"EM: Yeah, so we've been\nsort of puttering around"},{"time":426080,"text":"with the Hyperloop stuff for a while."},{"time":428720,"text":"We built a Hyperloop test track\nadjacent to SpaceX,"},{"time":432560,"text":"just for a student competition,"},{"time":434720,"text":"to encourage innovative\nideas in transport."},{"time":437760,"text":"And it actually ends up being\nthe biggest vacuum chamber in the world"},{"time":442800,"text":"after the Large Hadron Collider,"},{"time":445800,"text":"by volume."},{"time":449320,"text":"So it was quite fun to do that,\nbut it was kind of a hobby thing,"},{"time":454800,"text":"and then we think we might --"},{"time":458520,"text":"so we've built a little pusher car\nto push the student pods,"},{"time":464440,"text":"but we're going to try seeing\nhow fast we can make the pusher go"},{"time":468400,"text":"if it's not pushing something."},{"time":470720,"text":"So we're cautiously optimistic"},{"time":473080,"text":"we'll be able to be faster\nthan the world's fastest bullet train"},{"time":478120,"text":"even in a .8-mile stretch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480400,"text":"CA: Whoa. Good brakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482960,"text":"EM: Yeah, I mean, it's -- yeah."},{"time":485240,"text":"It's either going to smash\ninto tiny pieces or go quite fast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489880,"text":"CA: But you can picture,\nthen, a Hyperloop in a tunnel"},{"time":493480,"text":"running quite long distances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495320,"text":"EM: Exactly."},{"time":497040,"text":"And looking at tunneling technology,"},{"time":498840,"text":"it turns out that\nin order to make a tunnel,"},{"time":501400,"text":"you have to --"},{"time":504320,"text":"In order to seal against the water table,"},{"time":506720,"text":"you've got to typically design\na tunnel wall to be good"},{"time":511400,"text":"to about five or six atmospheres."},{"time":515159,"text":"So to go to vacuum is only one atmosphere,"},{"time":518200,"text":"or near-vacuum."},{"time":519640,"text":"So actually, it sort of turns out\nthat automatically,"},{"time":524080,"text":"if you build a tunnel that is good enough\nto resist the water table,"},{"time":528080,"text":"it is automatically\ncapable of holding vacuum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530520,"text":"CA: Huh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532160,"text":"EM: So, yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533720,"text":"CA: And so you could actually picture,"},{"time":535600,"text":"what kind of length tunnel\nis in Elon's future to running Hyperloop?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":541320,"text":"EM: I think there's no real length limit."},{"time":544560,"text":"You could dig as much as you want."},{"time":547600,"text":"I think if you were to do something"},{"time":549840,"text":"like a DC-to-New York Hyperloop,"},{"time":555040,"text":"I think you'd probably want\nto go underground the entire way"},{"time":557920,"text":"because it's a high-density area."},{"time":559560,"text":"You're going under\na lot of buildings and houses,"},{"time":563640,"text":"and if you go deep enough,"},{"time":565200,"text":"you cannot detect the tunnel."},{"time":567600,"text":"Sometimes people think,\nwell, it's going to be pretty annoying"},{"time":570560,"text":"to have a tunnel dug under my house."},{"time":572440,"text":"Like, if that tunnel is dug"},{"time":573800,"text":"more than about three or four\ntunnel diameters beneath your house,"},{"time":577000,"text":"you will not be able\nto detect it being dug at all."},{"time":580880,"text":"In fact, if you're able\nto detect the tunnel being dug,"},{"time":587600,"text":"whatever device you are using,"},{"time":589240,"text":"you can get a lot of money\nfor that device from the Israeli military,"},{"time":592530,"text":"who is trying to detect\ntunnels from Hamas,"},{"time":595636,"text":"and from the US Customs and Border patrol\nthat try and detect drug tunnels."},{"time":600440,"text":"So the reality is"},{"time":603680,"text":"that earth is incredibly good\nat absorbing vibrations,"},{"time":607560,"text":"and once the tunnel depth\nis below a certain level,"},{"time":610560,"text":"it is undetectable."},{"time":612560,"text":"Maybe if you have a very sensitive\nseismic instrument,"},{"time":615160,"text":"you might be able to detect it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617280,"text":"CA: So you've started\na new company to do this"},{"time":619680,"text":"called The Boring Company."},{"time":621400,"text":"Very nice. Very funny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":624760,"text":"EM: What's funny about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":626280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628920,"text":"CA: How much of your time is this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631600,"text":"EM: It's maybe ..."},{"time":635680,"text":"two or three percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637440,"text":"CA: You've bought a hobby."},{"time":638760,"text":"This is what an Elon Musk\nhobby looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642560,"text":"EM: I mean, it really is, like --"},{"time":645040,"text":"This is basically interns\nand people doing it part time."},{"time":651320,"text":"We bought some second-hand machinery."},{"time":656040,"text":"It's kind of puttering along,\nbut it's making good progress, so --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":660000,"text":"CA: So an even bigger part of your time"},{"time":661920,"text":"is being spent on electrifying\ncars and transport through Tesla."},{"time":667440,"text":"Is one of the motivations\nfor the tunneling project"},{"time":670040,"text":"the realization that actually,"},{"time":672600,"text":"in a world where cars are electric\nand where they're self-driving,"},{"time":676040,"text":"there may end up being\nmore cars on the roads"},{"time":679600,"text":"on any given hour than there are now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":682000,"text":"EM: Yeah, exactly."},{"time":686040,"text":"A lot of people think\nthat when you make cars autonomous,"},{"time":690360,"text":"they'll be able to go faster\nand that will alleviate congestion."},{"time":695000,"text":"And to some degree that will be true,"},{"time":696920,"text":"but once you have shared autonomy\nwhere it's much cheaper to go by car"},{"time":702000,"text":"and you can go point to point,"},{"time":704960,"text":"the affordability of going in a car\nwill be better than that of a bus."},{"time":710120,"text":"Like, it will cost less than a bus ticket."},{"time":712360,"text":"So the amount of driving that will occur\nwill be much greater with shared autonomy,"},{"time":717440,"text":"and actually traffic will get far worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720320,"text":"CA: You started Tesla\nwith the goal of persuading the world"},{"time":724600,"text":"that electrification\nwas the future of cars,"},{"time":727760,"text":"and a few years ago,\npeople were laughing at you."},{"time":730160,"text":"Now, not so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732640,"text":"EM: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":735840,"text":"I don't know. I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738080,"text":"CA: But isn't it true that pretty much\nevery auto manufacturer"},{"time":741520,"text":"has announced\nserious electrification plans"},{"time":744560,"text":"for the short- to medium-term future?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"EM: Yeah. Yeah."},{"time":751280,"text":"I think almost every automaker\nhas some electric vehicle program."},{"time":756280,"text":"They vary in seriousness."},{"time":757560,"text":"Some are very serious\nabout transitioning entirely to electric,"},{"time":761880,"text":"and some are just dabbling in it."},{"time":765280,"text":"And some, amazingly,\nare still pursuing fuel cells,"},{"time":767720,"text":"but I think that won't last much longer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769880,"text":"CA: But isn't there a sense, though, Elon,"},{"time":771960,"text":"where you can now just declare victory\nand say, you know, \"We did it.\""},{"time":775680,"text":"Let the world electrify,\nand you go on and focus on other stuff?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":781520,"text":"EM: Yeah."},{"time":784320,"text":"I intend to stay with Tesla\nas far into the future as I can imagine,"},{"time":788920,"text":"and there are a lot of exciting\nthings that we have coming."},{"time":793600,"text":"Obviously the Model 3 is coming soon."},{"time":795800,"text":"We'll be unveiling the Tesla Semi truck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800120,"text":"CA: OK, we're going to come to this."},{"time":802080,"text":"So Model 3, it's supposed\nto be coming in July-ish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807080,"text":"EM: Yeah, it's looking quite good\nfor starting production in July."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811640,"text":"CA: Wow."},{"time":813040,"text":"One of the things\nthat people are so excited about"},{"time":815440,"text":"is the fact that it's got autopilot."},{"time":818680,"text":"And you put out this video a while back"},{"time":821040,"text":"showing what that technology\nwould look like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826400,"text":"EM: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827640,"text":"CA: There's obviously autopilot\nin Model S right now."},{"time":830170,"text":"What are we seeing here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":831560,"text":"EM: Yeah, so this is using\nonly cameras and GPS."},{"time":837600,"text":"So there's no LIDAR\nor radar being used here."},{"time":840120,"text":"This is just using passive optical,\nwhich is essentially what a person uses."},{"time":845200,"text":"The whole road system\nis meant to be navigated"},{"time":847720,"text":"with passive optical, or cameras,"},{"time":851800,"text":"and so once you solve cameras"},{"time":855160,"text":"or vision,"},{"time":857720,"text":"then autonomy is solved."},{"time":859240,"text":"If you don't solve vision,\nit's not solved."},{"time":862120,"text":"So that's why our focus is\nso heavily on having a vision neural net"},{"time":868160,"text":"that's very effective for road conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871400,"text":"CA: Right. Many other people\nare going the LIDAR route."},{"time":874040,"text":"You want cameras plus radar is most of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876920,"text":"EM: You can absolutely\nbe superhuman with just cameras."},{"time":880320,"text":"Like, you can probably do it\nten times better than humans would,"},{"time":883360,"text":"just cameras."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884640,"text":"CA: So the new cars being sold right now\nhave eight cameras in them."},{"time":889120,"text":"They can't yet do what that showed."},{"time":893480,"text":"When will they be able to?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896440,"text":"EM: I think we're still on track\nfor being able to go cross-country"},{"time":902200,"text":"from LA to New York by the end\nof the year, fully autonomous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906400,"text":"CA: OK, so by the end\nof the year, you're saying,"},{"time":910200,"text":"someone's going to sit in a Tesla\nwithout touching the steering wheel,"},{"time":914200,"text":"tap in \"New York,\" off it goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916720,"text":"EM: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917960,"text":"CA: Won't ever have to touch the wheel --\nby the end of 2017."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922280,"text":"EM: Yeah. Essentially,\nNovember or December of this year,"},{"time":926920,"text":"we should be able to go all the way\nfrom a parking lot in California"},{"time":931360,"text":"to a parking lot in New York,"},{"time":933040,"text":"no controls touched at any point\nduring the entire journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936800,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":938840,"text":"CA: Amazing."},{"time":940080,"text":"But part of that is possible"},{"time":941520,"text":"because you've already got a fleet\nof Teslas driving all these roads."},{"time":944960,"text":"You're accumulating a huge amount\nof data of that national road system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951440,"text":"EM: Yes, but the thing\nthat will be interesting"},{"time":954120,"text":"is that I'm actually fairly confident\nit will be able to do that route"},{"time":960960,"text":"even if you change the route dynamically."},{"time":964840,"text":"So, it's fairly easy --"},{"time":968040,"text":"If you say I'm going to be really good\nat one specific route, that's one thing,"},{"time":971800,"text":"but it should be able to go,\nreally be very good,"},{"time":976960,"text":"certainly once you enter a highway,"},{"time":978720,"text":"to go anywhere on the highway system"},{"time":981520,"text":"in a given country."},{"time":984040,"text":"So it's not sort of limited\nto LA to New York."},{"time":986360,"text":"We could change it\nand make it Seattle-Florida,"},{"time":989840,"text":"that day, in real time."},{"time":992400,"text":"So you were going from LA to New York."},{"time":994560,"text":"Now go from LA to Toronto."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998320,"text":"CA: So leaving aside\nregulation for a second,"},{"time":1001080,"text":"in terms of the technology alone,"},{"time":1003880,"text":"the time when someone\nwill be able to buy one of your cars"},{"time":1007720,"text":"and literally just take the hands\noff the wheel and go to sleep"},{"time":1011560,"text":"and wake up and find that they've arrived,"},{"time":1013640,"text":"how far away is that, to do that safely?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1015600,"text":"EM: I think that's about two years."},{"time":1017880,"text":"So the real trick of it\nis not how do you make it work"},{"time":1021280,"text":"say 99.9 percent of the time,"},{"time":1024240,"text":"because, like, if a car crashes\none in a thousand times,"},{"time":1028359,"text":"then you're probably still not going\nto be comfortable falling asleep."},{"time":1035520,"text":"You shouldn't be, certainly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040040,"text":"It's never going to be perfect."},{"time":1042960,"text":"No system is going to be perfect,"},{"time":1044720,"text":"but if you say it's perhaps --"},{"time":1048520,"text":"the car is unlikely to crash"},{"time":1050960,"text":"in a hundred lifetimes,\nor a thousand lifetimes,"},{"time":1054440,"text":"then people are like, OK, wow,\nif I were to live a thousand lives,"},{"time":1058360,"text":"I would still most likely\nnever experience a crash,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"then that's probably OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062400,"text":"CA: To sleep."},{"time":1063640,"text":"I guess the big concern of yours\nis that people may actually"},{"time":1066520,"text":"get seduced too early\nto think that this is safe,"},{"time":1068830,"text":"and that you'll have some horrible\nincident happen that puts things back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073400,"text":"EM: Well, I think that the autonomy system\nis likely to at least mitigate the crash,"},{"time":1079440,"text":"except in rare circumstances."},{"time":1082280,"text":"The thing to appreciate\nabout vehicle safety"},{"time":1084600,"text":"is this is probabilistic."},{"time":1088920,"text":"I mean, there's some chance that any time\na human driver gets in a car,"},{"time":1092400,"text":"that they will have an accident\nthat is their fault."},{"time":1095360,"text":"It's never zero."},{"time":1097440,"text":"So really the key threshold for autonomy"},{"time":1101840,"text":"is how much better does autonomy\nneed to be than a person"},{"time":1106280,"text":"before you can rely on it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107680,"text":"CA: But once you get\nliterally safe hands-off driving,"},{"time":1111120,"text":"the power to disrupt\nthe whole industry seems massive,"},{"time":1113960,"text":"because at that point you've spoken\nof people being able to buy a car,"},{"time":1118360,"text":"drops you off at work,\nand then you let it go"},{"time":1120520,"text":"and provide a sort of Uber-like\nservice to other people,"},{"time":1124520,"text":"earn you money,"},{"time":1125760,"text":"maybe even cover the cost\nof your lease of that car,"},{"time":1128240,"text":"so you can kind of get a car for free."},{"time":1130120,"text":"Is that really likely?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131400,"text":"EM: Yeah. Absolutely\nthis is what will happen."},{"time":1134280,"text":"So there will be a shared autonomy fleet"},{"time":1136280,"text":"where you buy your car"},{"time":1137560,"text":"and you can choose\nto use that car exclusively,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"you could choose to have it be used\nonly by friends and family,"},{"time":1144720,"text":"only by other drivers\nwho are rated five star,"},{"time":1149800,"text":"you can choose to share it sometimes\nbut not other times."},{"time":1156120,"text":"That's 100 percent what will occur."},{"time":1159440,"text":"It's just a question of when."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1161960,"text":"CA: Wow."},{"time":1163200,"text":"So you mentioned the Semi"},{"time":1165440,"text":"and I think you're planning\nto announce this in September,"},{"time":1168200,"text":"but I'm curious whether there's\nanything you could show us today?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171320,"text":"EM: I will show you\na teaser shot of the truck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1175200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1177720,"text":"It's alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1179680,"text":"CA: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1180920,"text":"EM: That's definitely a case\nwhere we want to be cautious"},{"time":1183640,"text":"about the autonomy features."},{"time":1186360,"text":"Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1187600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1189240,"text":"CA: We can't see that much of it,"},{"time":1190880,"text":"but it doesn't look like\njust a little friendly neighborhood truck."},{"time":1194120,"text":"It looks kind of badass."},{"time":1195400,"text":"What sort of semi is this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1199160,"text":"EM: So this is a heavy duty,\nlong-range semitruck."},{"time":1203760,"text":"So it's the highest weight capability"},{"time":1208040,"text":"and with long range."},{"time":1211120,"text":"So essentially it's meant to alleviate\nthe heavy-duty trucking loads."},{"time":1217280,"text":"And this is something which\npeople do not today think is possible."},{"time":1222600,"text":"They think the truck doesn't have enough\npower or it doesn't have enough range,"},{"time":1226360,"text":"and then with the Tesla Semi"},{"time":1228920,"text":"we want to show that no, an electric truck"},{"time":1231600,"text":"actually can out-torque any diesel semi."},{"time":1237640,"text":"And if you had a tug-of-war competition,"},{"time":1241800,"text":"the Tesla Semi\nwill tug the diesel semi uphill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1246880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1249160,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1251040,"text":"CA: That's pretty cool.\nAnd short term, these aren't driverless."},{"time":1254080,"text":"These are going to be trucks\nthat truck drivers want to drive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1258480,"text":"EM: Yes. So what will be\nreally fun about this"},{"time":1261120,"text":"is you have a flat torque RPM curve\nwith an electric motor,"},{"time":1266520,"text":"whereas with a diesel motor or any kind\nof internal combustion engine car,"},{"time":1270040,"text":"you've got a torque RPM curve\nthat looks like a hill."},{"time":1273840,"text":"So this will be a very spry truck."},{"time":1276800,"text":"You can drive this\naround like a sports car."},{"time":1279680,"text":"There's no gears.\nIt's, like, single speed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1282080,"text":"CA: There's a great movie\nto be made here somewhere."},{"time":1284560,"text":"I don't know what it is\nand I don't know that it ends well,"},{"time":1287360,"text":"but it's a great movie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1288600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1289640,"text":"EM: It's quite bizarre test-driving."},{"time":1292400,"text":"When I was driving the test prototype\nfor the first truck."},{"time":1296440,"text":"It's really weird,\nbecause you're driving around"},{"time":1298720,"text":"and you're just so nimble,\nand you're in this giant truck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1301840,"text":"CA: Wait, you've\nalready driven a prototype?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1305360,"text":"EM: Yeah, I drove it\naround the parking lot,"},{"time":1307480,"text":"and I was like, this is crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1308960,"text":"CA: Wow. This is no vaporware."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1311160,"text":"EM: It's just like,\ndriving this giant truck"},{"time":1313280,"text":"and making these mad maneuvers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1315280,"text":"CA: This is cool.\nOK, from a really badass picture"},{"time":1317760,"text":"to a kind of less badass picture."},{"time":1320400,"text":"This is just a cute house\nfrom \"Desperate Housewives\" or something."},{"time":1323760,"text":"What on earth is going on here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1326840,"text":"EM: Well, this illustrates\nthe picture of the future"},{"time":1329320,"text":"that I think is how things will evolve."},{"time":1332320,"text":"You've got an electric car\nin the driveway."},{"time":1334680,"text":"If you look in between\nthe electric car and the house,"},{"time":1338440,"text":"there are actually three Powerwalls\nstacked up against the side of the house,"},{"time":1342320,"text":"and then that house roof is a solar roof."},{"time":1345160,"text":"So that's an actual solar glass roof."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1347280,"text":"CA: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1348520,"text":"EM: That's a picture of a real --\nwell, admittedly, it's a real fake house."},{"time":1352800,"text":"That's a real fake house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1354480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1357600,"text":"CA: So these roof tiles,"},{"time":1359480,"text":"some of them have in them\nbasically solar power, the ability to --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1365640,"text":"EM: Yeah. Solar glass tiles"},{"time":1367360,"text":"where you can adjust\nthe texture and the color"},{"time":1372480,"text":"to a very fine-grained level,"},{"time":1374480,"text":"and then there's\nsort of microlouvers in the glass,"},{"time":1380080,"text":"such that when you're looking\nat the roof from street level"},{"time":1383560,"text":"or close to street level,"},{"time":1385280,"text":"all the tiles look the same"},{"time":1387680,"text":"whether there is a solar cell\nbehind it or not."},{"time":1394000,"text":"So you have an even color"},{"time":1397440,"text":"from the ground level."},{"time":1400960,"text":"If you were to look at it\nfrom a helicopter,"},{"time":1403080,"text":"you would be actually able\nto look through and see"},{"time":1405480,"text":"that some of the glass tiles have\na solar cell behind them and some do not."},{"time":1409520,"text":"You can't tell from street level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1411160,"text":"CA: You put them in the ones\nthat are likely to see a lot of sun,"},{"time":1414240,"text":"and that makes these roofs\nsuper affordable, right?"},{"time":1416640,"text":"They're not that much more expensive\nthan just tiling the roof."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1419640,"text":"EM: Yeah."},{"time":1421840,"text":"We're very confident\nthat the cost of the roof"},{"time":1425840,"text":"plus the cost of electricity --"},{"time":1429920,"text":"A solar glass roof will be less\nthan the cost of a normal roof"},{"time":1432880,"text":"plus the cost of electricity."},{"time":1434320,"text":"So in other words,"},{"time":1435600,"text":"this will be economically a no-brainer,"},{"time":1439960,"text":"we think it will look great,"},{"time":1441680,"text":"and it will last --"},{"time":1443840,"text":"We thought about having\nthe warranty be infinity,"},{"time":1446920,"text":"but then people thought,"},{"time":1448160,"text":"well, that might sound\nlike were just talking rubbish,"},{"time":1450760,"text":"but actually this is toughened glass."},{"time":1456400,"text":"Well after the house has collapsed"},{"time":1459320,"text":"and there's nothing there,"},{"time":1461240,"text":"the glass tiles will still be there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1464800,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1466400,"text":"CA: I mean, this is cool."},{"time":1468160,"text":"So you're rolling this out\nin a couple week's time, I think,"},{"time":1471040,"text":"with four different roofing types."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1473600,"text":"EM: Yeah, we're starting off\nwith two, two initially,"},{"time":1476160,"text":"and the second two\nwill be introduced early next year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1479360,"text":"CA: And what's the scale of ambition here?"},{"time":1481440,"text":"How many houses do you believe\ncould end up having this type of roofing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1487760,"text":"EM: I think eventually"},{"time":1490560,"text":"almost all houses will have a solar roof."},{"time":1495880,"text":"The thing is to consider\nthe time scale here"},{"time":1499440,"text":"to be probably on the order"},{"time":1501920,"text":"of 40 or 50 years."},{"time":1505120,"text":"So on average, a roof\nis replaced every 20 to 25 years."},{"time":1511400,"text":"But you don't start replacing\nall roofs immediately."},{"time":1514760,"text":"But eventually,\nif you say were to fast-forward"},{"time":1518120,"text":"to say 15 years from now,"},{"time":1521600,"text":"it will be unusual to have a roof\nthat does not have solar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1525840,"text":"CA: Is there a mental model thing\nthat people don't get here"},{"time":1528720,"text":"that because of the shift in the cost,\nthe economics of solar power,"},{"time":1533160,"text":"most houses actually have\nenough sunlight on their roof"},{"time":1537280,"text":"pretty much to power all of their needs."},{"time":1539360,"text":"If you could capture the power,"},{"time":1541280,"text":"it could pretty much\npower all their needs."},{"time":1543360,"text":"You could go off-grid, kind of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1544920,"text":"EM: It depends on where you are"},{"time":1546480,"text":"and what the house size is\nrelative to the roof area,"},{"time":1549760,"text":"but it's a fair statement to say"},{"time":1551640,"text":"that most houses in the US\nhave enough roof area"},{"time":1556480,"text":"to power all the needs of the house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1559800,"text":"CA: So the key to the economics"},{"time":1563000,"text":"of the cars, the Semi, of these houses"},{"time":1567040,"text":"is the falling price\nof lithium-ion batteries,"},{"time":1570960,"text":"which you've made a huge bet on as Tesla."},{"time":1573480,"text":"In many ways, that's almost\nthe core competency."},{"time":1575760,"text":"And you've decided"},{"time":1578040,"text":"that to really, like, own that competency,"},{"time":1583280,"text":"you just have to build\nthe world's largest manufacturing plant"},{"time":1586760,"text":"to double the world's supply\nof lithium-ion batteries,"},{"time":1589920,"text":"with this guy. What is this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1592240,"text":"EM: Yeah, so that's the Gigafactory,"},{"time":1595720,"text":"progress so far on the Gigafactory."},{"time":1598440,"text":"Eventually, you can sort of roughly see"},{"time":1600360,"text":"that there's sort of\na diamond shape overall,"},{"time":1603320,"text":"and when it's fully done,\nit'll look like a giant diamond,"},{"time":1607960,"text":"or that's the idea behind it,"},{"time":1610200,"text":"and it's aligned on true north."},{"time":1611720,"text":"It's a small detail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1613480,"text":"CA: And capable of producing, eventually,"},{"time":1617400,"text":"like a hundred gigawatt hours\nof batteries a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1620600,"text":"EM: A hundred gigawatt hours.\nWe think probably more, but yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1623600,"text":"CA: And they're actually\nbeing produced right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1626000,"text":"EM: They're in production already.\nCA: You guys put out this video."},{"time":1629200,"text":"I mean, is that speeded up?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1630560,"text":"EM: That's the slowed down version."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1632280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1634080,"text":"CA: How fast does it actually go?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1636440,"text":"EM: Well, when it's running at full speed,"},{"time":1639280,"text":"you can't actually see the cells\nwithout a strobe light."},{"time":1643240,"text":"It's just blur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1644540,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1648000,"text":"CA: One of your core ideas, Elon,\nabout what makes an exciting future"},{"time":1651600,"text":"is a future where we no longer\nfeel guilty about energy."},{"time":1655480,"text":"Help us picture this."},{"time":1656920,"text":"How many Gigafactories, if you like,\ndoes it take to get us there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1661960,"text":"EM: It's about a hundred, roughly."},{"time":1663720,"text":"It's not 10, it's not a thousand."},{"time":1665480,"text":"Most likely a hundred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1668040,"text":"CA: See, I find this amazing."},{"time":1669720,"text":"You can picture what it would take"},{"time":1673720,"text":"to move the world\noff this vast fossil fuel thing."},{"time":1677000,"text":"It's like you're building one,"},{"time":1679600,"text":"it costs five billion dollars,"},{"time":1682480,"text":"or whatever, five to 10 billion dollars."},{"time":1684640,"text":"Like, it's kind of cool\nthat you can picture that project."},{"time":1688280,"text":"And you're planning to do, at Tesla --\nannounce another two this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1693480,"text":"EM: I think we'll announce locations"},{"time":1696360,"text":"for somewhere between two\nand four Gigafactories later this year."},{"time":1700120,"text":"Yeah, probably four."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1702040,"text":"CA: Whoa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1703680,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1706320,"text":"No more teasing from you for here?"},{"time":1710400,"text":"Like -- where, continent?"},{"time":1715480,"text":"You can say no."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1717440,"text":"EM: We need to address a global market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1721240,"text":"CA: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1722480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1723840,"text":"This is cool."},{"time":1727480,"text":"I think we should talk for --"},{"time":1732560,"text":"Actually, double mark it."},{"time":1734200,"text":"I'm going to ask you one question\nabout politics, only one."},{"time":1738320,"text":"I'm kind of sick of politics,\nbut I do want to ask you this."},{"time":1741600,"text":"You're on a body now\ngiving advice to a guy --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1747960,"text":"EM: Who?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1749200,"text":"CA: Who has said he doesn't\nreally believe in climate change,"},{"time":1752120,"text":"and there's a lot of people out there\nwho think you shouldn't be doing that."},{"time":1756480,"text":"They'd like you to walk away from that."},{"time":1758400,"text":"What would you say to them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1760720,"text":"EM: Well, I think that first of all,"},{"time":1764360,"text":"I'm just on two advisory councils"},{"time":1766920,"text":"where the format consists\nof going around the room"},{"time":1769760,"text":"and asking people's opinion on things,"},{"time":1772680,"text":"and so there's like a meeting\nevery month or two."},{"time":1777560,"text":"That's the sum total of my contribution."},{"time":1780800,"text":"But I think to the degree\nthat there are people in the room"},{"time":1783600,"text":"who are arguing in favor\nof doing something about climate change,"},{"time":1788360,"text":"or social issues,"},{"time":1794520,"text":"I've used the meetings I've had thus far"},{"time":1797760,"text":"to argue in favor of immigration\nand in favor of climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1802640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1804600,"text":"And if I hadn't done that,"},{"time":1806720,"text":"that wasn't on the agenda before."},{"time":1809560,"text":"So maybe nothing will happen,\nbut at least the words were said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1814680,"text":"CA: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1815920,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1819800,"text":"So let's talk SpaceX and Mars."},{"time":1823360,"text":"Last time you were here,"},{"time":1824840,"text":"you spoke about what seemed like\na kind of incredibly ambitious dream"},{"time":1828560,"text":"to develop rockets\nthat were actually reusable."},{"time":1832880,"text":"And you've only gone and done it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1835040,"text":"EM: Finally. It took a long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1836680,"text":"CA: Talk us through this.\nWhat are we looking at here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1839280,"text":"EM: So this is one of our rocket boosters"},{"time":1841440,"text":"coming back from\nvery high and fast in space."},{"time":1846040,"text":"So just delivered the upper stage"},{"time":1849320,"text":"at high velocity."},{"time":1851440,"text":"I think this might have been\nat sort of Mach 7 or so,"},{"time":1855320,"text":"delivery of the upper stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1858880,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1861840,"text":"CA: So that was a sped-up --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1863360,"text":"EM: That was the slowed down version."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1865200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1866560,"text":"CA: I thought that was\nthe sped-up version."},{"time":1869080,"text":"But I mean, that's amazing,"},{"time":1870440,"text":"and several of these failed"},{"time":1871800,"text":"before you finally\nfigured out how to do it,"},{"time":1874760,"text":"but now you've done this,\nwhat, five or six times?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1877680,"text":"EM: We're at eight or nine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1880000,"text":"CA: And for the first time,"},{"time":1881640,"text":"you've actually reflown\none of the rockets that landed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1884800,"text":"EM: Yeah, so we landed the rocket booster"},{"time":1887600,"text":"and then prepped it for flight again\nand flew it again,"},{"time":1890240,"text":"so it's the first reflight\nof an orbital booster"},{"time":1895440,"text":"where that reflight is relevant."},{"time":1897440,"text":"So it's important to appreciate\nthat reusability is only relevant"},{"time":1900640,"text":"if it is rapid and complete."},{"time":1905400,"text":"So like an aircraft or a car,"},{"time":1908680,"text":"the reusability is rapid and complete."},{"time":1911080,"text":"You do not send your aircraft\nto Boeing in-between flights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1916160,"text":"CA: Right. So this is allowing you\nto dream of this really ambitious idea"},{"time":1921000,"text":"of sending many, many, many people to Mars"},{"time":1924200,"text":"in, what, 10 or 20 years time, I guess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1926640,"text":"EM: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1928040,"text":"CA: And you've designed\nthis outrageous rocket to do it."},{"time":1931480,"text":"Help us understand\nthe scale of this thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1933920,"text":"EM: Well, visually\nyou can see that's a person."},{"time":1940680,"text":"Yeah, and that's the vehicle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1942520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1944200,"text":"CA: So if that was a skyscraper,"},{"time":1945960,"text":"that's like, did I read that,\na 40-story skyscraper?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1949320,"text":"EM: Probably a little more, yeah."},{"time":1952360,"text":"The thrust level of this is really --"},{"time":1958360,"text":"This configuration is about four times\nthe thrust of the Saturn V moon rocket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1964440,"text":"CA: Four times the thrust of the biggest\nrocket humanity ever created before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1969320,"text":"EM: Yeah. Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1972640,"text":"CA: As one does.\nEM: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1974120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1977120,"text":"In units of 747, a 747 is only about\na quarter of a million pounds of thrust,"},{"time":1983120,"text":"so for every 10 million pounds of thrust,"},{"time":1986240,"text":"there's 40 747s."},{"time":1987960,"text":"So this would be the thrust equivalent\nof 120 747s, with all engines blazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1994240,"text":"CA: And so even with a machine\ndesigned to escape Earth's gravity,"},{"time":1998480,"text":"I think you told me last time"},{"time":1999920,"text":"this thing could actually\ntake a fully loaded 747,"},{"time":2003200,"text":"people, cargo, everything,"},{"time":2005560,"text":"into orbit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2006840,"text":"EM: Exactly. This can take\na fully loaded 747 with maximum fuel,"},{"time":2012000,"text":"maximum passengers,\nmaximum cargo on the 747 --"},{"time":2016520,"text":"this can take it as cargo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2020080,"text":"CA: So based on this,"},{"time":2021840,"text":"you presented recently\nthis Interplanetary Transport System"},{"time":2026680,"text":"which is visualized this way."},{"time":2030080,"text":"This is a scene you picture in, what,\n30 years time? 20 years time?"},{"time":2034880,"text":"People walking into this rocket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2037480,"text":"EM: I'm hopeful it's sort of\nan eight- to 10-year time frame."},{"time":2042080,"text":"Aspirationally, that's our target."},{"time":2044480,"text":"Our internal targets\nare more aggressive, but I think --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2047520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2051600,"text":"CA: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2052840,"text":"EM: While vehicle seems quite large"},{"time":2055000,"text":"and is large by comparison\nwith other rockets,"},{"time":2057199,"text":"I think the future spacecraft"},{"time":2061199,"text":"will make this look like a rowboat."},{"time":2066320,"text":"The future spaceships\nwill be truly enormous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2071040,"text":"CA: Why, Elon?"},{"time":2073239,"text":"Why do we need to build a city on Mars"},{"time":2077400,"text":"with a million people\non it in your lifetime,"},{"time":2080480,"text":"which I think is kind of\nwhat you've said you'd love to do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2084480,"text":"EM: I think it's important to have"},{"time":2089120,"text":"a future that is inspiring and appealing."},{"time":2091880,"text":"I just think there have to be reasons"},{"time":2094679,"text":"that you get up in the morning\nand you want to live."},{"time":2097640,"text":"Like, why do you want to live?"},{"time":2099120,"text":"What's the point? What inspires you?"},{"time":2100880,"text":"What do you love about the future?"},{"time":2102760,"text":"And if we're not out there,"},{"time":2104280,"text":"if the future does not include\nbeing out there among the stars"},{"time":2108320,"text":"and being a multiplanet species,"},{"time":2110040,"text":"I find that it's incredibly depressing"},{"time":2112560,"text":"if that's not the future\nthat we're going to have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2115920,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2120120,"text":"CA: People want to position this\nas an either or,"},{"time":2122480,"text":"that there are so many desperate things\nhappening on the planet now"},{"time":2126200,"text":"from climate to poverty\nto, you know, you pick your issue."},{"time":2130480,"text":"And this feels like a distraction."},{"time":2133040,"text":"You shouldn't be thinking about this."},{"time":2134880,"text":"You should be solving what's here and now."},{"time":2137080,"text":"And to be fair, you've done\na fair old bit to actually do that"},{"time":2140040,"text":"with your work on sustainable energy."},{"time":2142880,"text":"But why not just do that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2147360,"text":"EM: I think there's --"},{"time":2152840,"text":"I look at the future\nfrom the standpoint of probabilities."},{"time":2157280,"text":"It's like a branching\nstream of probabilities,"},{"time":2161480,"text":"and there are actions that we can take\nthat affect those probabilities"},{"time":2167920,"text":"or that accelerate one thing\nor slow down another thing."},{"time":2172000,"text":"I may introduce something new\nto the probability stream."},{"time":2178840,"text":"Sustainable energy\nwill happen no matter what."},{"time":2181040,"text":"If there was no Tesla,\nif Tesla never existed,"},{"time":2183560,"text":"it would have to happen out of necessity."},{"time":2186440,"text":"It's tautological."},{"time":2188040,"text":"If you don't have sustainable energy,\nit means you have unsustainable energy."},{"time":2191720,"text":"Eventually you will run out,"},{"time":2193360,"text":"and the laws of economics\nwill drive civilization"},{"time":2199200,"text":"towards sustainable energy,"},{"time":2200880,"text":"inevitably."},{"time":2202120,"text":"The fundamental value\nof a company like Tesla"},{"time":2205120,"text":"is the degree to which it accelerates\nthe advent of sustainable energy,"},{"time":2209560,"text":"faster than it would otherwise occur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2213120,"text":"So when I think, like,"},{"time":2214360,"text":"what is the fundamental good\nof a company like Tesla,"},{"time":2217120,"text":"I would say, hopefully,"},{"time":2218840,"text":"if it accelerated that by a decade,\npotentially more than a decade,"},{"time":2224480,"text":"that would be quite a good thing to occur."},{"time":2226640,"text":"That's what I consider to be"},{"time":2228280,"text":"the fundamental\naspirational good of Tesla."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2233480,"text":"Then there's becoming a multiplanet\nspecies and space-faring civilization."},{"time":2239840,"text":"This is not inevitable."},{"time":2241800,"text":"It's very important to appreciate\nthis is not inevitable."},{"time":2244520,"text":"The sustainable energy future\nI think is largely inevitable,"},{"time":2247640,"text":"but being a space-faring civilization\nis definitely not inevitable."},{"time":2252400,"text":"If you look at the progress in space,"},{"time":2256600,"text":"in 1969 you were able\nto send somebody to the moon."},{"time":2260040,"text":"1969."},{"time":2262840,"text":"Then we had the Space Shuttle."},{"time":2265760,"text":"The Space Shuttle could only\ntake people to low Earth orbit."},{"time":2269200,"text":"Then the Space Shuttle retired,"},{"time":2270760,"text":"and the United States\ncould take no one to orbit."},{"time":2274320,"text":"So that's the trend."},{"time":2275600,"text":"The trend is like down to nothing."},{"time":2279560,"text":"People are mistaken when they think"},{"time":2281960,"text":"that technology\njust automatically improves."},{"time":2284080,"text":"It does not automatically improve."},{"time":2286000,"text":"It only improves if a lot of people\nwork very hard to make it better,"},{"time":2290680,"text":"and actually it will, I think,\nby itself degrade, actually."},{"time":2296480,"text":"You look at great civilizations\nlike Ancient Egypt,"},{"time":2298920,"text":"and they were able to make the pyramids,"},{"time":2300880,"text":"and they forgot how to do that."},{"time":2302720,"text":"And then the Romans,\nthey built these incredible aqueducts."},{"time":2305560,"text":"They forgot how to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2308720,"text":"CA: Elon, it almost seems,\nlistening to you"},{"time":2310800,"text":"and looking at the different\nthings you've done,"},{"time":2313080,"text":"that you've got this unique\ndouble motivation on everything"},{"time":2315880,"text":"that I find so interesting."},{"time":2319720,"text":"One is this desire to work\nfor humanity's long-term good."},{"time":2324320,"text":"The other is the desire\nto do something exciting."},{"time":2326680,"text":"And often it feels like you feel\nlike you need the one to drive the other."},{"time":2331400,"text":"With Tesla, you want\nto have sustainable energy,"},{"time":2334520,"text":"so you made these super sexy,\nexciting cars to do it."},{"time":2339080,"text":"Solar energy, we need to get there,"},{"time":2340800,"text":"so we need to make these beautiful roofs."},{"time":2342777,"text":"We haven't even spoken\nabout your newest thing,"},{"time":2345000,"text":"which we don't have time to do,"},{"time":2346560,"text":"but you want to save humanity from bad AI,"},{"time":2348920,"text":"and so you're going to create\nthis really cool brain-machine interface"},{"time":2352240,"text":"to give us all infinite memory\nand telepathy and so forth."},{"time":2356120,"text":"And on Mars, it feels\nlike what you're saying is,"},{"time":2358840,"text":"yeah, we need to save humanity"},{"time":2362560,"text":"and have a backup plan,"},{"time":2363960,"text":"but also we need to inspire humanity,"},{"time":2367240,"text":"and this is a way to inspire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2373680,"text":"EM: I think the value\nof beauty and inspiration"},{"time":2377480,"text":"is very much underrated,"},{"time":2379480,"text":"no question."},{"time":2381080,"text":"But I want to be clear."},{"time":2382360,"text":"I'm not trying to be anyone's savior."},{"time":2384200,"text":"That is not the --"},{"time":2386240,"text":"I'm just trying to think about the future"},{"time":2390040,"text":"and not be sad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2392400,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2394520,"text":"CA: Beautiful statement."},{"time":2398200,"text":"I think everyone here would agree"},{"time":2399800,"text":"that it is not --"},{"time":2401800,"text":"None of this is going\nto happen inevitably."},{"time":2403880,"text":"The fact that in your mind,\nyou dream this stuff,"},{"time":2407560,"text":"you dream stuff that no one else\nwould dare dream,"},{"time":2410160,"text":"or no one else\nwould be capable of dreaming"},{"time":2412840,"text":"at the level of complexity that you do."},{"time":2416520,"text":"The fact that you do that, Elon Musk,\nis a really remarkable thing."},{"time":2419720,"text":"Thank you for helping us all\nto dream a bit bigger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2422440,"text":"EM: But you'll tell me if it ever\nstarts getting genuinely insane, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2425960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2428480,"text":"CA: Thank you, Elon Musk.\nThat was really, really fantastic."},{"time":2431600,"text":"That was really fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2433040,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}